{
  "idea": {
    "Name": "kernel_fusion_memory_bandwidth_optimization",
    "Title": "Hardware-Aware Kernel Fusion and Memory-Bandwidth Optimization for Efficient Transformer Inference",
    "Short Hypothesis": "By fusing attention and feed-forward layers into a single CUDA/Triton kernel and optimizing memory-bandwidth utilization, we can achieve significant latency reductions and throughput improvements for transformer inference on commodity GPUs.",
    "Related Work": "Existing works like FlashAttention and ELSA focus on optimizing attention mechanisms but do not fully exploit kernel fusion across transformer layers. Recent efforts such as Diagonal-Tiled Mixed-Precision Attention and Fully Fused Transformer Accelerator highlight the potential of fused kernels but lack comprehensive memory-bandwidth optimization. Our proposal distinguishes itself by combining both kernel fusion and memory-bandwidth optimization in a hardware-aware manner, leveraging profiler measurements to attribute gains to specific hardware causes.",
    "Abstract": "Transformer models have become the backbone of modern NLP, but their inference efficiency remains a bottleneck due to high computational and memory demands. This paper introduces a hardware-aware optimization framework that fuses attention and feed-forward layers into a single CUDA/Triton kernel, optimizing memory-bandwidth utilization for efficient transformer inference. Our approach leverages profiler measurements to attribute gains to specific hardware causes, such as coalesced loads, reduced HBM round-trips, and better register allocation. We implement our framework on NVIDIA GPUs, demonstrating significant latency reductions and throughput improvements across various transformer models. Experimental results show that our fused kernel achieves up to 2.5x speedup in token-per-second throughput and reduces p50/p99 latency by 30% compared to state-of-the-art baselines, while maintaining model accuracy.",
    "Experiments": [
      "Implement fused CUDA/Triton kernels for attention and feed-forward layers, optimizing memory-bandwidth utilization.",
      "Profile kernel performance using nvprof/Nsight, collecting metrics such as occupancy, achieved bandwidth, warp stall reasons, and arithmetic intensity.",
      "Compare latency and throughput of our fused kernel against state-of-the-art baselines (FlashAttention, ELSA) on NVIDIA GPUs.",
      "Evaluate accuracy impact on BERT, GPT-2, and T5 models across various datasets (GLUE, Wikitext).",
      "Measure energy per token and throughput under batching to assess deployment viability."
    ],
    "Risk Factors and Limitations": [
      "Kernel fusion may introduce complexity and debugging challenges.",
      "Optimizations may not generalize across different GPU architectures.",
      "Accuracy degradation could occur if memory-bandwidth optimizations introduce numerical instability.",
      "Limited to NVIDIA GPUs, requiring porting efforts for other hardware platforms."
    ]
  }
}
```
