aware compression using mutual information.', 'Evaluate the bounds on standard benchmarks (e.g., CIFAR-10, ImageNet) by comparing theoretical predictions with empirical compression performance using pruning and quantization.', 'Measure the mutual information between compressed model representations and task labels to validate the theoretical bounds.', 'Compare the generalization error of compressed models against the derived bounds to assess predictive sufficiency.'], 'Risk Factors and Limitations': ['Theoretical bounds may be difficult to compute exactly for large models due to the complexity of mutual information estimation.', 'Empirical validation relies on accurate estimation of task-relevant information, which can be challenging in high-dimensional spaces.', 'The framework assumes task-relevance can be fully captured by mutual information, which may not hold for all tasks.']}
