sed pruning on CIFAR-10 and ImageNet.', 'Develop a quantization scheme that allocates bits based on mutual information, benchmarking against uniform and mixed-precision quantization.', 'Evaluate performance using accuracy (task-specific), compression ratio, and bits-per-weight metrics.', 'Compare to existing rate-distortion-based methods (e.g., Isik et al., 2021) and mixed-precision techniques (e.g., EMQ, AMP-ViT).'], 'Risk Factors and Limitations': ['Estimating mutual information in high-dimensional spaces may introduce bias or variance, potentially affecting the bounds.', 'The method assumes task-specific compressibility, which may not hold for tasks requiring high-dimensional representations.', 'Computational overhead of mutual information estimation could limit scalability to very large models.', 'The framework relies on accurate task-specific mutual information, which may be challenging to estimate for complex tasks.']}
